						<summary>

						<p>Pillar lying by the road side in the village.</p>						

						<p>12th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to the 12th century A.D. on palaeography grounds.</p>						

						<p>It mentions king, <hi rend="italic">Purōhita, Daṇḍanāyaka, Sēnāpati, Karaṇamu</hi> and Bōya as witnesses.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and begining lost. Purport is not clear. Seems to refers to setting up of a pillar.</p>						

						</summary>
